[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating Gradle dependencies**\n\nI'm thinking that the driver can add extra dependencies. I want to inspect a simple code compilation with just the target dependency. Maybe using a temporary Gradle project would be helpful, but it might be costly to verify. I prefer not to modify the original repo, so using /tmp could work instead. I'll look into using the installed Gradle or the local .gradle, and I might create a simple temp setup instead. I need to decide on a precise list of dependencies.\n\n**Confirming Gradle dependencies**\n\nI’m considering whether the test uses internal classes or if public signatures are necessary. Deterministic dependencies shouldn’t duplicate transitive runtime that the Gradle test runtime already has. It seems I need to ensure that `compileClasspath` includes the runtime dependencies. Let’s confirm this by using `Gradle dependencyInsight`, and I think it would be best to implement a temporary build for testing this. Looking forward to making sure everything is set up correctly!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_06add6cff3c3bdec016a2866df3f80819391167ac5436b384c\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqKGbsnFDdC961wEdVknSDEufyJ3xZIuQBOlMXKJR-PoKtNn6r3xtCaxHQmRwplUV3en_z43cRdWi0G6y3ry9Yx1F8aoE4gwhIUVSI5FZ7eZerLmNIzC7X_Xn2kZSWNswqrTDjW56gsJQwRbngaRRCen9AhCDSN6iTqC1Swqa0dZj8sE9UpTft-7m5LSRTN7RJ97TecskKonpYCD8zv3-qBMrsK0Fa3VOqfDKfgCs0OwCP8bg6A8z9K2Q9fvJD0-Cfu5We12ZGTjMBzkfH--jt7dNvFU_sj-iRNDE-GZoDMyCu4g9BhqMwQ5kL6tUGwrdYdNcjwkbfgAo0g11GLEhKmKY2Q9ju9SysdA71Hbmoiw0aON2-efD-EcYvE1oONez65hRj2k6V8HkLm0G0nuMpo3JAXNsagRGooWmpmdowx4v2kt7yiQ3f99OnM2G2vcKOgcs4zzfjHYC_oc8iOnHO0tkVh9XmWZyMKUOWQVYqRkug8MrXS4e3pZsyuL8LmdkY_rGg7lFjiD0iCE2beftYi5tJ82G5nIubKMzsFG2ICfqX352DyRGfDf7a5n1k2279xILocoxlCqJqY66lsuB-n8feHtKusKHagqMnwZsf6lUEsPCAHlXyRPHVENAJfwEGOV1_ACbflQWC_syw8frVBgXaKcrz5rjcHQGwOjvdBFNBek-bCktStbvQ2hYoVnNTJ